What is private offline is private and online
Private.
According to a dictionary published by the Royal Spanish Academy, it is something of a personal nature or "the area of private life that everyone has the right to protect against any breach".
What is privacy for a person under 16?
How does he apply this definition in his daily life and social networks?
He understands the dangers he is exposed to when he publishes things on the Internet that he would certainly not tell anyone during normal communication?
ElPerodoico journalists reported five boys and girls between the ages of 10 and 15 who are frequent Internet users.
In four cases, they considered the concept of privacy to be "something entirely own" on a personal level and "user name and password" when it was a social network.
