"Social networks are fun, I can talk to relatives who are far or fast to communicate with friends," he says.
Without hesitation, he says he would never accept an application from an unknown person.
He wouldn't even care if someone recommended someone he didn't know.
The case of 14-year-old José is different.
This teenager owns accounts on Hotmail, Facebook, My Space and Ask networks and on the last mentioned network admits that he does not know 20 people from his list of friends.
"I'm not afraid of it because we have something in common, like music," he says.
According to this boy, none of them led him to anything, nor did he want an address or a phone number.
"If they insist on me or demand it from me, I will simply remove them from my account," he admits.
José applied to Ask after reading the recommendation on Twitter.
These boys are not strangers to what is now called cyberbullying.
