Key questions
Marielos Porrasová, an English teacher and graduate of the field of education and teaching, believes that to inform children and adolescents in social networks, they need to understand that the main purpose of these networks is to inform them.
He states: "The Internet was created as a means of finding information, but when social networks appeared, the rules of the game changed."
Marrielos Porrasová notes that academic worker Marc Prensky, graduate of teaching at Yale University and author of the article Digital Domestics and Digital Migrants introduced these concepts to explain this phenomenon.
"Digital natives are children and young people who were born at the time of this technology.
