According to this specialist, it is the most effective way for children and adolescents to show what privacy is, to ask questions that make them think.
"Telling them not to do anything, it doesn't work," he adds.
Marrielos Porrasová also mentions some of the possibilities: Are there things you wouldn't tell a stranger, so why do you do it on the Internet?
Or would you like someone to publish your picture the way you published your friend?
You know what everyone else says about you?
